---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<style>
  .section h2 { margin-bottom: 20px; }
  .section h3 { margin-top: 28px; margin-bottom: 14px; }
</style>

<Layout
  title="Privacy policy — Audioask"
  description="Audioask (Natives Sàrl) privacy policy: data collected, purposes, your rights, GDPR and Swiss LPD compliance."
  lang="en"
  alternatePath="/confidentialite"
>

<section class="hero" style="padding-top: 80px; padding-bottom: 60px; min-height: auto;">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="hero-copy" style="max-width: 720px;">
      <p class="eyebrow">Legal</p>
      <h1 style="font-size: clamp(2rem, 4vw, 2.8rem);">Privacy policy</h1>
      <p class="lede">At Audioask, protecting your personal data is a priority. This document describes what data we collect, how we use it, and what your rights are.</p>
      <p style="color: var(--ink-3); font-size: 0.875rem;">Last updated: June 2026</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section paper">
  <div class="container" style="max-width: 820px;">
    <h2>1. Data controller</h2>
    <p>The data controller responsible for processing your personal data is:</p>
    <p>
      <strong>Natives Sàrl</strong><br>
      Carouge, Canton of Geneva, Switzerland<br>
      Service: Audioask — <a href="https://audioask.ai">audioask.ai</a>
    </p>
    <p>For any questions about your personal data, contact us via <a href="/en/contact">/en/contact</a>.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section alt">
  <div class="container" style="max-width: 820px;">
    <h2>2. Data collected</h2>

    <h3>Account data</h3>
    <p>When you create an account via Auth0, we collect:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Your email address</li>
      <li>Your name (if provided)</li>
      <li>Authentication information managed by Auth0</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Service usage data</h3>
    <p>When you use Audioask, we collect:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Audio files or podcast links submitted for transcription</li>
      <li>Transcriptions generated and the prompts you write</li>
      <li>AI analysis results</li>
      <li>Your credit usage history</li>
      <li>Technical usage logs (date, time, actions performed)</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Billing data</h3>
    <p>Payment data is processed directly by our provider Paddle (see section 5). We do not store your bank details or credit card numbers.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section paper">
  <div class="container" style="max-width: 820px;">
    <h2>3. Purposes of processing</h2>
    <p>Your data is used for the following purposes:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Service delivery:</strong> audio transcription, AI analysis, podcast automation, bookmarks, and automation management.</li>
      <li><strong>Account management:</strong> authentication, service communications, customer support.</li>
      <li><strong>Billing and subscription management:</strong> via our partner Paddle.</li>
      <li><strong>Service improvement:</strong> aggregated and anonymized usage analysis to improve features.</li>
      <li><strong>Legal obligations:</strong> retention of data required by applicable law.</li>
    </ul>
    <p>We do not sell your data to third parties and do not use it for advertising purposes. Some of these purposes involve carefully selected technical providers bound by data processing agreements compliant with GDPR and the Swiss LPD.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section alt">
  <div class="container" style="max-width: 820px;">
    <h2>4. Retention periods</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Account data (email, name):</strong> for the duration of your subscription, then 2 years after account closure.</li>
      <li><strong>Transcriptions, prompts, and results:</strong> for the duration of your active subscription, deleted on request or upon account closure.</li>
      <li><strong>Technical logs:</strong> 90 rolling days.</li>
      <li><strong>Billing data:</strong> in accordance with applicable legal and accounting obligations (generally 10 years under Swiss law).</li>
    </ul>
    <p>After these periods, your data is securely deleted or anonymized.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section paper">
  <div class="container" style="max-width: 820px;">
    <h2>5. Cookies</h2>
    <p>Audioask uses only strictly necessary cookies:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Auth0 session cookies:</strong> maintaining your login session.</li>
      <li><strong>Functional cookies:</strong> remembering your interface preferences.</li>
    </ul>
    <p>We use <strong>no advertising cookies, third-party tracking cookies, or tracking pixels</strong>. No data is shared with advertising networks.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section alt">
  <div class="container" style="max-width: 820px;">
    <h2>6. Your rights</h2>
    <p>Under the GDPR and the Swiss Federal Act on Data Protection (LPD), you have the following rights:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Right of access:</strong> obtain a copy of the data we hold about you.</li>
      <li><strong>Right to rectification:</strong> correct inaccurate or incomplete data.</li>
      <li><strong>Right to erasure:</strong> request deletion of your personal data.</li>
      <li><strong>Right to portability:</strong> receive your data in a structured, machine-readable format.</li>
      <li><strong>Right to object:</strong> object to certain processing of your data.</li>
      <li><strong>Right to restriction:</strong> request restriction of processing in certain circumstances.</li>
    </ul>
    <p>To exercise these rights, contact us via <a href="/en/contact">/en/contact</a>. We will respond within 30 days.</p>
    <p>If you believe that the processing of your data is not in compliance with applicable law, you have the right to lodge a complaint with the <strong>Swiss Federal Data Protection and Information Commissioner (FDPIC)</strong>.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section paper">
  <div class="container" style="max-width: 820px;">
    <h2>7. Data security</h2>
    <p>We implement appropriate technical and organizational measures to protect your data against unauthorized access, loss, destruction, or disclosure. All communications between your browser and our servers are encrypted via HTTPS/TLS.</p>
    <p>In the event of a data breach likely to result in a high risk to your rights and freedoms, we will notify you within the timeframes required by applicable law.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section alt">
  <div class="container" style="max-width: 820px;">
    <h2>8. Applicable law and jurisdiction</h2>
    <p>This privacy policy is governed by Swiss law, in particular the Federal Act on Data Protection (LPD) and its implementing ordinance (OLPD).</p>
    <p>Any dispute relating to the protection of your personal data will be subject to the jurisdiction of the <strong>Canton of Geneva</strong>, Switzerland.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section paper">
  <div class="container" style="max-width: 820px;">
    <h2>9. Changes to this policy</h2>
    <p>Natives Sàrl reserves the right to amend this privacy policy at any time. In the event of a material change, we will notify you by email or via an in-app notification.</p>
    <p>The current version is always available at <a href="https://audioask.ai/en/privacy">audioask.ai/en/privacy</a>. The date of last update appears at the top of this document.</p>
  </div>
</section>

</Layout>
